TASK 01: WRITING BETTER PROMPTS
OBJECTIVE
Learn the fundamentals of prompt engineering by transforming vague prompts into clear, specific, and effective prompts. Prompt engineering helps users communicate their requirements clearly to AI systems, resulting in more accurate, relevant, and useful responses. This task demonstrates how the quality of a prompt directly affects the quality of the output generated by an AI model.
INTRODUCTION
A prompt is the instruction or question given to an AI system. Well-structured prompts provide context, define the audience, specify the desired format, and set clear expectations. Poor prompts often lead to generic responses, while detailed prompts generate focused and actionable results.
EXAMPLES
Example 1
Vague Prompt: Explain climate change.
Improved Prompt: Explain climate change in 3 simple bullet points for a 12-year-old student.
Example 2
Vague Prompt: Tell me about Python.
Improved Prompt: Explain Python programming basics for beginners with 5 practical examples.
Example 3
Vague Prompt: Write an email.
Improved Prompt: Write a professional email to a hiring manager thanking them for the interview.
Example 4
Vague Prompt: Give me fitness advice.
Improved Prompt: Create a 7-day fitness plan for a beginner who can exercise 30 minutes per day.
Example 5
Vague Prompt: Explain SQL.
Improved Prompt: Explain SQL joins with simple examples using employee and department tables.
ANALYSIS
The improved prompts provide clear instructions, a specific target audience, a defined output format, relevant context, and measurable expectations. These enhancements reduce ambiguity and help AI systems generate more accurate, focused, and useful responses.
BENEFITS OF EFFECTIVE PROMPTS
Improves response accuracy
Reduces ambiguity and confusion
Saves time by minimizing follow-up questions
Produces structured and relevant outputs
Enhances productivity and decision-making
CONCLUSION
Effective prompts improve AI responses by providing clear guidance and sufficient context. Including details such as audience, format, tone, constraints, and purpose helps generate high-quality outputs. Prompt engineering is an essential skill for maximizing the performance of Large Language Models (LLMs) and achieving better results in real-world applications.
